ğŸ“‹ Step 5.2: Create Send OTP and Verify OTP APIs (Django Backend)
Now we move to Send OTP and Verify OTP â€”
These are needed before allowing the user to complete signup.

ğŸ“‹ Plan for OTP
Send OTP API: When user enters Email/Phone â†’ system generates OTP â†’ temporarily saves OTP linked to the user.

Verify OTP API: User enters OTP â†’ system verifies the OTP.

âœ… For simplicity, we will store OTP temporarily inside the database (in a new model).

ğŸ› ï¸ Steps to Implement OTP System
1. Update users/models.py to create OTP Model
Add this below your CustomUser model in users/models.py:

python
Copy
Edit
import random

class OTP(models.Model):
    user = models.OneToOneField(CustomUser, on_delete=models.CASCADE)
    code = models.CharField(max_length=6)
    created_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)

    def __str__(self):
        return f"OTP for {self.user.email}"
âœ… This will store:

User linked to OTP

OTP code

Creation time

